The Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC), on Thursday,said it arrested a Computer Science Undergraduate of the University of Port Harcourt (UNIPORT), Kenneth Gift, 22 for alleged cybercrimes. Operatives also nabbed his girlfriend, Dandy Spice, and his mother, Dorah Aninah, in Agbor, Delta State. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-817472 size-full" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/po3.jpg" alt="" width="744" height="992" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/po3.jpg 744w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/po3-225x300.jpg 225w" sizes="(max-width: 744px) 100vw, 744px"> All suspects were apprehended for alleged internet fraud. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-817473 size-full" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/po5.jpg" alt="" width="744" height="992" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/po5.jpg 744w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/po5-225x300.jpg 225w" sizes="(max-width: 744px) 100vw, 744px"> EFCC spokesman, Dele Oyewale, announced the operation in a statement. The trio’s arrest was sequel to a petition from the US Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI). A 5-bedroom duplex has been recovered from them. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-817474 size-large" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/po2-1024x519.jpg" alt="" width="740" height="375" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/po2-1024x519.jpg 1024w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/po2-300x152.jpg 300w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/po2.jpg 1080w" sizes="(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px"> Others are Mercedes-Benz CA250, Mercedes-Benz C250, Mercedes Benz GLK 350, laptop computers and mobile phones. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-817475 size-large" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/po1-768x1024.jpg" alt="" width="740" height="987" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/po1-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/po1-225x300.jpg 225w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/po1.jpg 810w" sizes="(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px"> “The suspects have made useful statements and will be charged to court as soon investigations are completed”, Oyewale added.